org.check_m_model.msg: Some metabolites are missing their formula
org.check_m_model.to_do: Correct the formulas of the listed metabolites. Some metabolite formulas are critical for the completion of this pipeline. If homology is ON, this pipeline will try to fill in the formulas from the reference.

org.check_m_model.msg: Some metabolites have a problematic formula. If these metabolites are used in protein modifications, or other subreactions, it will cause an error.
org.check_m_model.to_do: Correct the formulas of the listed metabolites. Some metabolite formulas are critical for the completion of this pipeline. If homology is ON, this pipeline will try to fill in the formulas from the reference.

org.check_m_model.msg: Some reactions are missing their subsystem
org.check_m_model.to_do: Make sure the subsystems of these reactions are correct

org.check_gene_overlap.msg: M-model has a 21 gene overlap with optional files (BioCyc)
org.check_gene_overlap.to_do: Check whether optional files where downloaded correctly.

org.generate_complexes_df.msg: Some proteins have no genes in proteins.txt

org.sync_files.msg: The types of some genes (e.g. CDS, RNA...) could not be identified. Is Product or Gene Name missing?
org.sync_files.to_do: Manually fill the products (with types) of these genes in genes.txt

org.check_for_duplicates.msg: Some datasets contain duplicate indices or Accession IDs.
org.check_for_duplicates.to_do: Remove or fix duplicates. If duplicates are in Accession-1, they are processed as different possibilities to get the same enzyme, so they are added as generic complexes. Check!

org.update_genbank_from_files.msg: Some feature in genbank are CDS but have no translation qualifier. Translated sequences from Biopython were filled in instead
org.update_genbank_from_files.to_do: Check whether the genbank was downloaded or constructed correctly.

org.get_rpod.msg: FY484_RS02755-MONOMER was identified as RpoD. If this is not true, define RpoD!
org.get_rpod.to_do: Check whether you need to correct RpoD by running me_builder.org.rpod = correct_rpod

org.get_rna_polymerase.msg: CPLX2G6Z-10 was identified as RNA polymerase
org.get_rna_polymerase.to_do: Check whether you need to correct RNAP by running me_builder.org.get_rna_polymerase(force_RNAP_as=correct_RNAP)

org.get_TU_df.msg: Some genes appear in TUs.txt but not in genes.txt
org.get_TU_df.to_do: If those genes are supposed to be in the model, fill them in genes.txt

org.get_TU_df.msg: Some TUs are either empty (no genes in TUs.txt) or contain genes that are not in genes.txt
org.get_TU_df.to_do: If those TUs contain genes that are supposed to be in the model, fill them in TUs.txt and genes.txt

org.update_ribosome_stoich.msg: Some ribosomal proteins do not contain subunit information (30S, 50S). Check whether they are ribosomal proteins!

org.purge_genes_in_model.msg: Some genes in M-model were not found in genes.txt or genome.gb. These genes will be skipped in reconstruction.
org.purge_genes_in_model.to_do: Confirm the gene is correct in the m_model. If so, add it to genes.txt

update_ribosome_subreactions_from_homolo.to_do: Confirm whether the definitions or homology calls are correct in me_builder.org.ribosome_subreactions. Curate the inputs in ribosome_subreactions.txt accordingly.
